title: Google\Cloud\Dlp\V2\ReidentifyContentRequest
name: ReidentifyContentRequest
description:
Request to re-identify an item.

Generated from protobuf message google.privacy.dlp.v2.ReidentifyContentRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description:
Required. Parent resource name. The format of this value varies depending on whether you have specified a processing location: + Projects scope, location specified:
projects/PROJECT_ID/locations/LOCATION_ID + Projects scope, no location specified (defaults to global):
projects/PROJECT_ID The following example parent string specifies a parent project with the identifier example-project, and specifies the europe-west3 location for processing data: parent=projects/example-project/locations/europe-west3

params.name: data.reidentify_config
params.description: Configuration for the re-identification of the content item. This field shares the same proto message type that is used for de-identification, however its usage here is for the reversal of the previous de-identification. Re-identification is performed by examining the transformations used to de-identify the items and executing the reverse. This requires that only reversible transformations be provided here. The reversible transformations are: - CryptoDeterministicConfig - CryptoReplaceFfxFpeConfig

params.name: data.item
params.description: The item to re-identify. Will be treated as text.

params.name: data.inspect_template_name
params.description: Template to use. Any configuration directly specified in inspect_config will override those set in the template. Singular fields that are set in this request will replace their corresponding fields in the template. Repeated fields are appended. Singular sub-messages and groups are recursively merged.

params.name: data.reidentify_template_name
params.description: Template to use. References an instance of DeidentifyTemplate. Any configuration directly specified in reidentify_config or inspect_config will override those set in the template. The DeidentifyTemplate used must include only reversible transformations. Singular fields that are set in this request will replace their corresponding fields in the template. Repeated fields are appended. Singular sub-messages and groups are recursively merged.

methods.name: getReidentifyConfig

Configuration for the re-identification of the content item.

This field shares the same proto message type that is used for de-identification, however its usage here is for the reversal of the previous de-identification.
